text: Year 5 BC was a common year starting on Monday or Tuesday of the Julian calendar. At the time, it was known as the Year of the Consulship of Augustus and Sulla. == Births == * Emperor Guangwu of Han, ruler of China (d. AD 57) * Lucius Vitellius the Elder, Roman consul and Governor of Syria (d. AD 51) * John the Baptist (possible date) * Jesus (possible date) ==References==
title: 5 BC
